## 2026-07-18 17:03 CEST
Built the Phase 0 eval harness: backend/eval/answer_key.yaml (machine-readable F1-F4 schemes and D1-D7 decoys from data/info.md, verified against the sample DuckDB, scoring-only — never enters prompts) and backend/scripts/eval.py (full / --reuse-batch / --score-only modes scoring scheme recall, decoy false positives and wall-clock vs the 10-min budget, archiving each run under backend/eval/runs/ and exiting non-zero below target); added pyyaml dependency.

## 2026-07-18 17:20 CEST
Built the Phase 1 deterministic check library (backend/app/checks/): 9 generalizable JET checks (new-vendor profile, missing goods receipt, creator=approver SoD, permission concentration, repair vocabulary in assets, cut-off unaccrued, threshold-split clusters, round amounts, off-hours stats) over a fuzzy table/column resolver, runnable via python -m app.checks and wired into the pipeline and eval harness with checks.json persisted per batch; also fixed scripts/smoke_test.py for the streaming agent API.

## 2026-07-18 17:40 CEST
Wired Phase 2 of the fraud pipeline: the analysis agent is now fed the deterministic check candidates and must report-or-rule-out each one (new ruled_out output + RuledOut model, checklist/"empty is a failure" prompt, list_checks/run_check tools, raised tool-round budget). Switched the default model to openai:gpt-5.6-sol with a configurable reasoning effort after gpt-5.1 stalled on a single turn. Live eval on the sample dossier now scores 4/4 schemes, 0 decoys, in ~188s (down from 0/4).

## 2026-07-18 17:50 CEST
Rewrote the root README.md into a project overview covering the fraud-audit pipeline, stack, how to run it, and current vs planned phases from the reliable detection plan.

## 2026-07-18 17:50 CEST
Added Phase 4 verifier pass (backend/app/agent/verifier.py): an independent second-opinion agent re-derives every finding via SQL and returns confirmed/uncertain/refuted; refuted findings move to ruled_out, and each finding's likelihood is replaced by a corroboration-driven confidence based on the count of distinct documents whose cited rows actually resolve. Added FindingVerification/VerificationReport models and source_count/verified/verification_note fields (mirrored in frontend types), wired verification into the pipeline and eval harness (AUDITOR_VERIFY toggle). Live eval holds 4/4 schemes, 0 decoys in ~289s with F1 scored across 5 independent sources.

